### ARIA Support in Ink's Box Component (JavaScript)

Source: https://context7.com/vadimdemedes/ink/llms.txt

The Box component in Ink supports ARIA attributes for accessibility, including various `aria-role` values and `aria-state` properties. This allows for semantic labeling and state communication to assistive technologies like screen readers. It requires the Ink library.

```javascript
import {render, Box, Text} from 'ink';

function AccessibleForm() {
  return (
    <Box flexDirection="column">
      <Box aria-role="textbox" aria-state={{required: true, multiline: false}}>
        <Text>Username: </Text>
      </Box>

      <Box aria-role="checkbox" aria-state={{checked: false, disabled: false}}>
        <Text>☐ Remember me</Text>
      </Box>

      <Box aria-role="button" aria-label="Submit form">
        <Text>Submit</Text>
      </Box>
    </Box>
  );
}

render(<AccessibleForm />);
```

