### Write string to stdout while preserving Ink output

Source: https://github.com/vadimdemedes/ink/blob/master/readme.md

The write() method from useStdout allows writing strings to stdout without conflicting with Ink's rendering. Output appears above Ink's normal rendering area. Similar to Static component but only accepts strings, not React components.

```javascript
import {useStdout} from 'ink';

const Example = () => {
	const {write} = useStdout();

	useEffect(() => {
		// Write a single message to stdout, above Ink's output
		write('Hello from Ink to stdout\n');
	}, []);

	return …
};
```

