### Measure Element Dimensions with measureElement

Source: https://github.com/vadimdemedes/ink/blob/master/readme.md

Provides an example of using the measureElement function to get the width and height of a Box component. It highlights the importance of using useEffect for accurate measurements after the initial render.

```jsx
import {render, measureElement, Box, Text} from 'ink';
import React, {useRef, useEffect} from 'react';

const Example = () => {
	const ref = useRef();

	useEffect(() => {
		const {width, height} = measureElement(ref.current);
		// width will be 100, height will be 1
	}, []);

	return (
		<Box width={100}>
			<Box ref={ref}>
				<Text>This box will stretch to 100 width</Text>
			</Box>
		</Box>
	);
};

render(<Example />);
```
